{
  "title": "Properties",
  "descriptions": [
    "The website is built with a defined set of visual properties. The visual properties are encapsulated in functional CSS classes and are appended to the <a class=\"no-underline bb b--light-gray space-gray dim\" href=\"http://tachyons.io/\" target=\"_blank\">Tachyons</a> library. The website uses function-based styling for immutability, reusability, and scalability.",

    "The classes use a slightly different naming convention than the default Tachyons naming convention. Instead of appending the scale value to the end of a class, the site appends the final <span class=\"roboto-mono\">rem</span> value for easier readability and faster editing. For example, <span class=\"roboto-mono\">.h5</span> is equivalent to <span class=\"roboto-mono\">{ height: 5rem; }</span> and <span class=\"roboto-mono\">.ma4</span> is equivalent to <span class=\"roboto-mono\">{ margin: 4rem; }</span>."
  ],
